On Thu, Dec 6, 2012 at 7:34 AM, Monty Rowden <montyrowden(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> Im thinking of a tin-top conversion, with a 1776cc type1 style engine..... or is that
going to overheat?

Big jugs on a bus engine are not going to be helpful without
corresponding changes in stroke. Ronnie builds an 1800 single port
stroker for buses that you might want to look into. I think it uses
1600 jugs and gets the added displacement through stroke.

John
